  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The association between position of upper gastrointestinal endoscopy (EGD) and saliva droplet
      spreading has never been studied. In the era of contagious viral spreading, this pilot study
      is aimed to assess adenosine triphosphate (ATP) at the face shield of endoscopist which can
      represent the saliva droplet spreading of patients in left lateral and prone position during
      EGD.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
